@node Cap02 "Requirements"
  =======================================================================
  To install 5D-LastCallers you must have the following things:

    Programm        Location                  Description
    ----------      --------                  -----------
    5D-LastCallers  BBS:Utils/5D-LastCallers  Main program

  - an  Amiga Model (500/600/1000/1200/2000/2500/3000/4000/CDTV/CDł˛)
  - the installed Version of OS\2, OS\3 or higher
    (Soft- or Hardware Version)
  - the installed .INFO Files in the directories.
  - AmiExpress v3.xx or higher.

  =======================================================================
@endnode
@node Cap03 "How to install 5D-LastCallers"
  =======================================================================
  To install 5D-LastCallers you must have all Requirement which were
  mentioned below. You need the following things.

  --------------------------
    BBS:Utils/ (dir)
      ^^^ 5D-LastCallers
  --------------------------

  Decruch the 5D-LastCallers Archive. Go to your 'BBS:Utils/' Directory.
  Copy '5D-LastCallers' into the Directory. Go to your LogOff-Batch(s) and
  insert the following:

  Usage  : 5D-LastCallers <NODE NUMBER> <OUTPUT FILE> <USERS> <MODE> {UP_DESC} {DOWN_DESC}

  *** EXAMPLE OF LOGOFF BATCH FOR NODE 1 ***

  ###CUT###
  BBS:Utils/5D-LastCallers/5D-LastCallers 1 Bulletins:Bull1.TXT 14 1 NO_FILE S:LC.TXT
  ###CUT###

  <> = HAS TO BE USED
  {} = CAN BE USED

  If you possibly want to have a .txt under the bull but not before you can use NO_FILE
  for the <UP/DOWN_DESC> or if ya onyl want the output file to be maken you simply
  write ONLY_OUTPUT instead of da node number! <MODE> can be between 0 and 2!!!

  =======================================================================
@endnode
